1.question: Which method performs the best when trained with only 1% of the MNIST training data, and how much does data augmentation improve its performance in this scenario?
1.answer: When trained with only 1% of the MNIST training data, ITN (B-CNN) (w/ DA) performs the best with a testing error of 2.78%. Data augmentation further improves its performance by 0.4%, bringing the testing error down to 2.78% from 3.18% achieved by ITN (B-CNN) without data augmentation.

2.question: How does the ITN framework generate pseudo-negative samples?
2.answer: The ITN framework generates pseudo-negative samples by applying learned transformations to positive samples.
